Tanzania Reduces Gasoline, Diesel, Kerosene Prices, Energy Regulator Says

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-08-03T05:13:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/tanzania-reduces-gasoline-diesel-kerosene-prices-energy-regulator-says.html
Tanzania reduced gasoline, diesel and
kerosene prices with immediate effect, according to the East
African nationâ€™s energy regultor.  The price of gasoline has been cut by 9.2 percent, diesel
by 8.3 percent and kerosene by 8.7 percent, the Dar es Salaam-
based Energy and Water Utilities Regulatory Authority said in a
statement published in the Daily News newspaper today.  Gasoline now costs 2,004 shillings per liter in Dar es
Salaam, while diesel costs 1,911 shillings and kerosene 1,905
shillings, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
